Introduction

Choi Yena mononymously known as Yena is a South Korean singer, rapper, guitarist, songwriter, host, and actress under Yuehua Entertainment and former Polaris Entertainment trainee. Yena was the main rapper, lead vocalist, and lead dancer of the project girl group IZ*ONE. She ranked #4 in the hit survival show Produce48 with 285,385 votes, earning her a spot in the group.

Yena made her debut as a member of IZ*ONE on October 29, 2018, with their first mini album "COLOR*IZ" with "La Vie en Rose" serving as the title track. After two years and six months of successful promotions, they disbanded on April 29, 2021. This led Yena to pursue solo activities.

Yena participated in a variety of shows, such as the "Idol Dictation Contest" and the "Girls High School Mystery Class." She also made her acting debut through the second season of Naver TV Cast's "The World of My 17" where she played the female lead role.

On January 17, 2022, Yena made her highly-anticipated solo debut with the mini album "Smiley."
